ure out why getDeclaredMethod on HiddenSubclass isn't finding what I expect. It seems that getMethod is just returning the superclass method from PublicBase, and there's no IllegalAccess issue. I need a public method in the hidden class with the same signature to make this trigger properly. I wonder if I can use an assertion like \\\"hidden:x\\\" to see if it invokes the hidden override through the superclass method's dynamic dispatch.\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_MA1wqBt7bpobpHLzISyNSw9b|fc_07b20893e79efca1016a2738d19d4c81969cb9489e52b8445d", "name": "read", "arguments": {"path": "../../source_context/org.mozilla/rhino/1.7R5/main/extracted/rhino1_7R5/src/org/mozilla/javascript/serialize/ScriptableOutputStream.java", "offset": 34, "limit": 95}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 1332, "output": 1973, "cacheRead": 31744, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 35049, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1780955297534, "responseId": "resp_07b20893e79efca1016a2738a211e08196b42686cad8eccf62"}}
