[recv] {"type": "turn_end", "message": {"role": "assistant", "content": [{"type": "thinking", "thinking": "**Evaluating class access in Java**\n\nI'm thinking about how the `readMember` method interacts with `declaring.getConstructor(parms)`. This is where it gets tricky: does `getConstructor` only pertain to public classes? It seems that `getConstructor` indeed returns only public constructors for a given class. If a class isn’t public, but its constructor is, I wonder if it would still retrieve that constructor. It appears that class accessibility and constructor accessibility are separate in this context.\n\n**Evaluating method access in subclasses**\n\nI'm trying to figure out why getDeclaredMethod on HiddenSubclass isn't finding what I expect. It seems that getMethod is just returning the superclass method from PublicBase, and there's no IllegalAccess issue. I need a public method in the hidden class with the same signature to make this trigger properly. I wonder if I can use an assertion like \"hidden:x\" to see if it invokes the hidden override through the superclass method's dynamic dispatch.", "thinkingSignature": "{\"id\":\"rs_07b20893e79efca1016a2738a2de40819689f94b912a141d57\",\"type\":\"reasoning\",\"content\":[],\"encrypted_content\":\"gAAAAABqJzjRaYSIOKgPxr3wLV-Lp9i84Ai-rk27mVpQ_zIi0i_FEw-JPXexTUkRYHVoHjdOLpO5sEAUdC_4dE3GceC1OUuQRp1q8l9M1dSzk00ZHW6zIAzZVSeaOHihRcBq289pHt99Vjbiqq9ISrCkPe6QXCXw5bNujuStChvVS67wNrQv8_7VwPYKflhjLcGVv1ZYkizW0a2vmE5oQ80IuWz8-hoTccYVjkvpic1zlK3C3p3j7tvLi4JalIhu30GUnuwpQmJephZHcXRRp7yv8aN9p8rc5W9Y6cETVxq6H4M6OZhhUZyGtsRWzuFZio6UqxyoFgho9aTOH8f5yF5wa2kVyg8RG9CNp9ah6JQD-ElqE7e2TOr0espbZH_zb3BvgYDGlVeD3WCQvGvMkNu6sUwvzLfNOe31b4kg5AJ8KCMpGbfH9GLb3GUWKdQhbk2VHhkmCpW3mNHrOHjzv5e03SadTwgP-EMil4htRepq2eM6xHWnC3dLo5X3C9Kr5p39OfpvGZZZsuPq1g0Nv1RUkD58KrW5_6LxyphNKY0YdSDX3IBaxH0at2y5u9c77Gn_kECYAniVh2wkvE79qxqmWFh3LDm47hRNFFbkDqeYxyjCL92griDYqjH4-Y6AO1VPHPIZQbq6QPcataM2RA32J4E8mQMRM1khoTAK834meHDr1MC22Z233xGKD6ct9FWeXbY84nKD41J1SUIqxwID-T