od. However, I need to ensure we don't use the `$` symbol in test class names. It seems that nested classes can have it, but not for test classes. I might also want to confirm that tests are under the target root and perhaps use `git diff` for checks.\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_T2IZ74t6FJtfI4rs4dGdfh8r|fc_07b20893e79efca1016a2739090a9481968dbe4bf15830de15", "name": "bash", "arguments": {"command": "git diff -- tests/src/org.mozilla/rhino/1.7R5/src/test/java/org_mozilla/rhino/MemberBoxTest.java"}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 301, "output": 865, "cacheRead": 37376, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 38542, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1780955372754, "responseId": "resp_07b20893e79efca1016a2738edf2208196854f366e20f5019f"}}
